# AC Drain Wiz – Product & Brand Knowledge

Use this rule plus `src/config/acdwKnowledge.ts` as the source of truth for product names, support details, and copy (including **`T_MANIFOLD_SPECS`** for Mini/Sensor T-manifold and bayonet dimensions). Do not invent specs, URLs, warranty terms, or compatibility claims not present in these sources.

## Products (official names and roles)

- **AC Drain Wiz Mini** (ACDW Mini): Drain line **maintenance access** device. Permanent service port on the 3/4" condensate drain line for flush (water), air (compressed air), and vacuum—no cutting PVC. One-time install, horizontal only; PVC solvent weld (e.g. Oatey All-Purpose Cement)—apply primer and cement only to the condensate line, then fit into the T manifold horizontal openings (not on the manifold openings).
  - **Transparent T-Manifold (same part as Sensor kits):** **5 3/8"** length (left PVC socket opening to right PVC socket opening) × **1 1/2"** overall height (including the bayonet top connection port) × **1 3/8"** height of each horizontal socket opening. **Horizontal sockets:** the **1 3/8"** dimension is the physical opening height; openings are **sized for standard 3/4" nominal PVC** condensate drain line (solvent weld). **Bayonet (top):** **1 5/8"** top opening. **Bayonet connectors:** Mini bi-directional valve base and Sensor Switch bayonet mating interface are **1 3/4"** diameter. Do not invent alternate values; do not use legacy `5" × 3" × 2"`. Canonical strings live in `T_MANIFOLD_SPECS` in `src/config/acdwKnowledge.ts`.
- **AC Drain Wiz Standard Sensor Switch**: **Non-WiFi** overflow protection. Capacitive sensing, automatic AC shutdown at 80% water level, no moving parts, fail-safe on power loss. **Does not require the Mini to install**—sensors include their own **same Transparent T-Manifold** as the Mini (identical part; dimensions in `T_MANIFOLD_SPECS`).
- **AC Drain Wiz WiFi Sensor Switch**: **WiFi** variant. Adds remote monitoring, email/SMS alerts, contractor app, service alerts between 50–79% (shutdown at 80%). **24V HVAC power is strongly recommended** for consistent LED feedback and reliable operation; battery-only operation is supported with limited LED visibility. Lithium-ion backup battery ~2 years; low-battery warning in platform. A fully depleted battery (battery-only path) may trigger protective HVAC shutdown.

**Relationship**: Sensor Switch installs in the same bayonet port as the Mini valve/cap. For service: remove Sensor → install Mini valve → clean → reinstall Sensor. Contractors can install Sensor-only (with its own manifold) without buying Mini first.

## Product naming and positioning

- Use **"AC Drain Wiz Mini"** and **"AC Drain Wiz Sensor"** as acceptable shorthand in UI/marketing when full names are too long.
- **Sensor variants—use consistently across the site:**
  - **Full name (when distinguishing):** "AC Drain Wiz Standard Sensor Switch (Non-WiFi)" and "AC Drain Wiz WiFi Sensor Switch". Use `SENSOR_STANDARD_DISPLAY` and `SENSOR_WIFI_DISPLAY` from `acdwKnowledge.ts`.
  - **Short label (tight spaces, e.g. card titles):** "Standard Sensor Switch (Non-WiFi)" and "WiFi Sensor Switch". Use `SENSOR_STANDARD_SHORT` and `SENSOR_WIFI_SHORT`.
  - Avoid standalone "Non-WiFi model" or "Non-WiFi Model" without "Standard Sensor Switch"; avoid "Wifi and Non-Wifi models".
- **Mini**: position as permanent service access, one-time installation, lifetime benefits, 35% faster clean-out, no cut-and-reattach.
- **Sensors**: position as overflow protection and (WiFi) predictive maintenance; avoid implying the Sensor "requires" the Mini for initial installation.

